nal letters [[Order of Jamaica|OJ]].<ref name=JamHonsGov2>[http://www.jis.gov.jm/special_sections/This%20Is%20Jamaica/awards.html National Awards of Jamaica] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130126142610/http://www.jis.gov.jm/special_sections/This%20Is%20Jamaica/awards.html |date=26 January 2013 }} Official Jamaican Government website</ref>

==Personal appearances==
Bolt made a cameo appearance in the opening sketch of 13 October 2012 broadcast of ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'', hosted by [[Christina Applegate]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.celebuzz.com/2012-10-14/saturday-night-live-recap-christina-applegate-is-a-californian-usain-bolt-strikes-twice-videos/ |title='Saturday Night Live' Recap: Christina Applegate is a 'Californian'; Usain Bolt Strikes Twice (Videos) |website=Celebuzz! |date=14 October 2012 |access-date=2 July 2021 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywood.com/tv/snl-recap-christina-applegate-gave-her-all-usain-bolt-grabbed-the-comedy-baton-57252284/ |title='SNL' Recap: Christina Applegate Gave Her All, Usain Bolt Grabbed the Comedy Baton |website=Hollywood.com |date=14 October 2012 |access-date=2 July 2021 }}</ref> The segment was a parody of the [[United States vice-presidential debate, 2012|Vice Presidential debate]] between [[Joe Biden]] and [[Paul Ryan]].<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.ibtimes.com/usain-bolt-tells-paul-ryan-snl-skit-846881 | title=Usain Bolt Tells Off Paul Ryan In 'SNL' Skit | first=Tom | last=Herrmann | work=International Business Times | date=15 October 2012 | accessdate=18 June 2021 }}</ref> In the sketch, [[Taran Killam]] mimicking Ryan had just [[Pseudologia fantastica|lied]] about running a 2:50 [[marathon]], a [[Four-minute mile|sub-4-minute mile]] on no training and winning the [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's 100 metres|100 metres in London]] when Bolt was introduced as his partner to confirm.{{Citation needed|date=February 2021}}

When Ryan asked Bolt "Who won the 100 metres?" the Jamaican gold-medallist answered simply. "I did." Ryan followed up by asking Bolt about his (Ryan's) finish. "You didn't finish. You weren't even there."<ref>{{cite news |last=Epstein |first=David |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/blogs/obnoxiousbostonfan/2012/10/snl_video_usain_bolt_vp_debate_biden_ryan.html |title=SNL: Bolt adds jolt to Ryan-Biden VP debate; Christina Applegate hosts – Obnoxious Boston Fan |work=Boston Globe |date=13 October 2012 |access-date=10 November 2012 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106231244/http://www.boston.com/sports/blogs/obnoxiousbostonfan/2012/10/snl_video_usain_bolt_vp_debate_biden_ryan.html |archive-date=6 November 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nbc.com/saturday-night-live/video/vice-presidential-debate-cold-open/n27745|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170807071017/http://www.nbc.com/saturday-night-live/video/vice-presidential-debate-cold-open/n27745?snl=1|url-status=dead|title=Vice Presidential Debate Cold Open|archive-date=7 August 2017|website=nbc.com}}</ref>

In November 2016, Bolt competed against [[James Corden]] in a rap battle on the "Drop the Mic" segment of ''[[The Late Late Show with James Corden]]'', which he won.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2016-11-24|title=Drop the Mic w/ Usain Bolt|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eQGgtVN0ZcI|access-date=2021-01-30|website=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>

In late October 2020, Bolt starred in the pilot episode of the cartoon ''SCRAM!'' produced by KidSuper and Puma as a [[Taxicab|taxi driver]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=2020-10-28|title=SCRAM! Cartoon Pilot Starring Usain Bolt, Hector Bellerin & More // Presented by KidSuper and PUMA|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gyf9NJOOgiM|access-date=2021-02-01|website=YouTube}}</ref>

