===Records===
Bolt's personal best of 9.58 seconds in 2009 in the 100 metres is the fastest ever run.<ref>{{cite web |title=100 Metres All Time |publisher=[[IAAF]] |date=5 August 2012 |url=http://www.iaaf.org/statistics/toplists/inout=O/age=N/season=0/sex=M/all=y/legal=A/disc=100/detail.html |access-date=14 August 2012 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120812054831/http://www.iaaf.org/statistics/toplists/inout%3Do/age%3Dn/season%3D0/sex%3DM/all%3Dy/legal%3DA/disc%3D100/detail.html |archive-date=12 August 2012  }}</ref> Bolt also holds the second fastest time of 9.63 seconds,<ref name=Berlindata/> the current Olympic record,<ref name=Top100/> and set two previous [[Men's 100 metres world record progression|world records]] in the event. Bolt's personal best of 19.19 s in the 200 metres is the world record. This was recorded at the [[2009 World Championships in Athletics]] in Berlin against a headwind of −0.3&nbsp;m/s. This performance broke his previous world record in the event, his 19.30 s clocking in winning the [[Athletics at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Men's 200 metres|2008 Olympic 200 metres title]].

Bolt has been on three world-record-setting Jamaican relay teams. The first record, 37.10 seconds, was set in winning gold at the [[Athletics at the 2008 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|2008 Summer Olympics]], although the result was voided in 2017 when the team was disqualified. The second record came at the [[2011 World Championships in Athletics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|2011 World Championships in Athletics]], a time of 37.04 seconds. The third world record was set at the [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|2012 Summer Olympics]], a time of 36.84 seconds.<ref>{{cite web |title=4x100 Metres Relay All Time |publisher=[[IAAF]] |date=22 August 2008 |url=http://www.iaaf.org/statistics/toplists/inout=O/age=N/season=0/sex=M/all=y/legal=A/disc=4x1/detail.htmx |access-date=14 August 2012 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020141641/http://www.iaaf.org/statistics/toplists/inout%3DO/age%3DN/season%3D0/sex%3DM/all%3Dy/legal%3DA/disc%3D4x1/detail.htmx |archive-date=20 October 2012  }}</ref>

Bolt also holds the 200 metres world teenage best results for the age categories 15 (20.58 s), 16 (20.13 s, former world youth record),<ref>Zaccardi, Nick (1 June 2021). [https://olympics.nbcsports.com/2021/06/01/erriyon-knighton-usain-bolt-olympics-track-and-field/ "Erriyon Knighton, 17-year-old pro sprinter, breaks Usain Bolt junior record"]. ''[[NBC Sports]]''. Retrieved 1 June 2021.</ref><ref>Mulkeen, Jon (1 June 2021). [https://www.worldathletics.org/competitions/world-athletics-continental-tour/news/erriyon-knighton-world-u18-best-200m "Knighton breaks Bolt’s world U18 200m best with 20.11 in Jacksonville"]. ''[[World Athletics]]''. Retrieved 1 June 2021.</ref> 17 (19.93 s) and 18 (19.93 s, [[List of world under-20 records in athletics|world junior record]]).<ref name=Berlindata>{{cite web|title=12th IAAF World Championships in Athletics: IAAF Statistics Handbook. Berlin 2009. |url=http://www.iaaf.org/mm/document/competitions/competition/05/15/63/20090706014834_httppostedfile_p345-688_11303.pdf |publisher=IAAF Media & Public Relations Department |location=Monte Carlo |page=410 |year=2009 |access-date=2 August 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090806172743/http://www.iaaf.org/mm/document/competitions/competition/05/15/63/20090706014834_httppostedfile_p345-688_11303.pdf |archive-date=6 August 2009 }}</ref> He also holds the 150 metres world best set in 2009, during which he ran the last 100 metres in 8.70 seconds, the quickest timed 100 metres ever.<ref name=Berlindata/>

Bolt completed a total of 53 wind-legal sub-10-second performances in the 100&nbsp;m during his career, with his first coming on 3 May 2008 and his last on 5 August 2017 at the World Championships. His longest undefeated streak in the 200&nbsp;m was in 17 finals, lasting from 12 June 2008 to 3 September 2011. He also had a win-streak covering 14 100&nbsp;m finals from 16 August 2008 to 16 July 2010.<ref>[http://www.tilastopaja.net/db/at.php?Sex=1&ID=45032 Usain Bolt]{{Dead link|date=January 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}. Tilastopaja. Retrieved 1 May 2018.</ref>

